m_q.target_metric: Average exceedance rate of marine beaches from 2002 to 2023 (inclusive), rounded to 2 decimal places

Calculate the number of violations for marine beaches for each year.
Divide the number of violations by the total number of samples for each year to get the exceedance rate.
Calculate the average of the yearly exceedance rates.

schema_conflicts: Violation column has inconsistent casing (YES/NO, Yes/No, yes/no)

format_notes: Sample Date is in datetime format.

constraints: Indicator Level must be a number.
Violation must be a categorical variable (Yes/No).
output_format_requirements: Output must be a single number rounded to 2 decimal places.
